HEADWORD: Ash Wednesday
<hw>Ash` Wednes"day</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧sh` w⟦ecr⟧nz"d⟦asl⟧)</pr>. <def>The
first day of Lent; -- so called from a custom in the Roman Catholic
church of putting ashes, on that day, upon the foreheads of
penitents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

